==Demographics==
[[Image:CarrollCountyMD.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Farm in Carroll County, Maryland]]
As of the [[census]][[Geographic references#2|<U+00B2>]] of 2000, there were 150,897 people, 52,503 households, and 41,109 families residing in the county.  The [[population density]] was 130/km<U+00B2> (336/mi<U+00B2>).  There were 54,260 housing units at an average density of 47/km<U+00B2> (121/mi<U+00B2>).  The racial makeup of the county was 95.69% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 2.28% [[Race (United States Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 0.22% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], 0.75% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 0.02% [[Race (United States Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.31% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.73% from two or more races.  0.99% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race. 30.5% were of [[german people|German]], 14.0% [[irish people|Irish]], 11.1% [[United States]] or American, 10.7% [[English people|English]] and 7.3% [[italian people|Italian]] ancestry according to [[Census 2000]].

There were 52,503 households out of which 39.70% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 66.50% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 8.30% had a female householder with no husband present, and 21.70% were non-families. 17.50% of all households were made up of individuals and 7.40% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.81 and the average family size was 3.18.

In the county the population was spread out with 27.70% under the age of 18, 7.00% from 18 to 24, 30.60% from 25 to 44, 23.90% from 45 to 64, and 10.80% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 37 years. For every 100 females there were 97.40 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 94.00 males.

The median income for a household in the county was $60,021, and the median income for a family was $66,430. Males had a median income of $44,191 versus $30,599 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the county was $23,829.  About 2.70% of families and 3.80% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 4.00% of those under age 18 and 4.90% of those age 65 or over.

